entries.title: 'It slowly spread like wildfire': Inside the dramatic symptoms of long Covid
entries.description: Jessica Rosario loved watching her 15-year-old, Eliana, play flute with the rest of the marching band during Open Door Christian School football games. But after the homecoming game in 2021, she got an alarming call from the Ohio school's band director.

entries.title: Fewer than 10 documents found at Biden's Delaware home were marked classified
entries.description: Fewer than 10 documents marked classified were found at President Joe Biden's residence in Wilmington, Delaware, according to multiple sources familiar with the investigation. None of the documents found at the home were top secret, the highest of the three basic levels of classification.

entries.title: 2 Earth-size worlds revealed beyond our solar system
entries.description: There are more than 5,000 known worlds beyond our solar system.

entries.title: China says 60,000 people have died of Covid since early December
entries.description: Close to 60,000 people have died of Covid in China since the country abruptly abandoned its tight "zero-Covid" policy in early December, a medical official from the National Health Commission (NHC) told a press conference in Beijing on Saturday.

entries.description: As President Joe Biden and Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida met privately in Tokyo last year, Biden delivered a message that was as strategic as it was genuine.

entries.title: 9 places where you can walk in MLK Jr.'s footsteps
entries.description: Martin Luther King Jr. was born and raised in the American South, but his dream of racial equality and social justice reverberated out of his region, into the whole country and around the world. And it wasn't just his vision that spanned the globe -- the man himself embarked on travels far and wide.
